# Local Persistence & Platform Services Review

## Local Persistence

Validate:
- all persistence isolated inside data layer
- repositories abstract implementation details
- JSON serialization in models, not entities
- `SharedPreferences` keys centralized in datasource
- read/write consistency (tasks + XP)
- graceful handling of corrupt/missing JSON

Future remote sync readiness requires:
- datasource isolation
- repository abstraction
- centralized serialization
- no `SharedPreferences` imports outside data layer
- transport-agnostic entities

## Platform Services

Validate:
- `NotificationService`, `LiveActivityService`, `ForegroundService` used only from presentation/services — never from domain
- timer lifecycle: start, update, stop/cleanup on complete or dispose
- iOS Live Activity and Android foreground service symmetry
- permissions requested at startup (`main.dart`)
- no leaked timers or background tasks after navigation away

---

# Security Review

Validate:
- no secrets hardcoded
- input validation on user-created content (task titles)
- safe JSON parsing with typed models
- platform permissions justified and documented
- no sensitive data in logs

Review for:
- unsafe logs
- missing validation
- insecure fallback behavior
- excessive permissions

DO NOT approve:
- hardcoded secrets
- raw `jsonDecode` without model validation in presentation
- sensitive logs
- bypassable input validation

---

# Performance Review

## Mobile Performance

Review:
- rebuild frequency
- memory allocation
- startup overhead (service initialization in `main`)
- animation controller disposal
- unnecessary async work
- battery impact from background timer/notifications

## Persistence Performance

Validate:
- save frequency (avoid saving entire task list on every micro-interaction if avoidable)
- JSON payload size growth
- startup load strategy (async init in `HomeScreen`)

